Two separate standard curves were established to estimate the copy number and GE of CLso and CLas present in the potato and citrus hairy roots, respectively (Supplementary Fig. 7). Briefly, a 76-bp amplicon corresponding to the 16S rDNA of CLso37 and an 81-bp amplicon corresponding to the nrdB gene of CLas40 were synthesized and cloned into the pUC57 vector (GenScript, NJ, USA)37. This plasmid was used as a template to generate the standard curves. Copy number of these targets was determined from the size of the amplified fragment (76 bp for CLso and 81 bp for CLas) and the size of the vector in which the fragment was cloned (2716 + 76 = 2792 bp for CLso and 2716 + 81 = 2797 bp for CLas). The molar mass of the plasmid was estimated in Daltons using Eq. 11\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
